wa: The CDC allows for testing of people with unexplained severe symptoms not linked to the flu. Previously, only those who had recently traveled to high-risk areas or had been exposed to the virus were eligible for testing. EvergreenHealth staff alert King County health officials that multiple patients have come from Life Care Center, including one with symptoms suspected to be COVID-19.

Public Health learns 20 residents are ill and that they tested negative for the flu. Another hospital reports a Life Care-related case. Shoreline lab begins testing. Preliminary test results come back positive for four cases, including two Life Care residents. County health officials contact the CDC and state officials.
